The paper is about a novel neural network architecture for sequence labeling tasks, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions that their system requires no feature engineering or data pre-processing, which suggests that it may involve some level of automatic feature learning or representation learning, making cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The use of bidirectional LSTM, CNN, and CRF also suggests that the paper may involve some level of deep learning and/or computer vision, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) possible sub-categories.
